{"name":"Lambent Strike","type":"feat","img":"icons/magic/fire/flame-burning-fist-strike.webp","system":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif\">Starting at 3rd level, you can make your ki resonate with elemental fire. When you make an unarmed attack on your turn, you can ignite the ki around body part you strike with. An unarmed strike made this way deals fire damage instead of bludgeoning damage.<br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" /><br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" />When you hit with this strike, you can deal 1d10 additional fire damage. You can add this extra damage a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, regaining expended uses when you finish a long rest. While you have no uses available, you can spend 1 ki point to activate the extra damage again.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"special","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":"","recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"other","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[["1d10","fire"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"class","subtype":"ki"},"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675045733071,"modifiedTime":1675050196252,"lastModifiedBy":"dWkJQvEoVSj5iz4H"},"_id":"YMIiby2UURDzfRIt","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"dWkJQvEoVSj5iz4H":3}}
{"name":"Extra Attack","type":"feat","img":"icons/weapons/swords/sword-guard-red-jewel.webp","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Starting at 5th level, you can attack twice instead of once when you take the Attack action on your turn. You can choose to cast a warmage cantrip instead of one (and only one) of the weapon attacks.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"","subtype":""},"requirements":"Warmage 5","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ZTw1HNvVe0dYcEXM"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675139030225,"modifiedTime":1675141148234,"lastModifiedBy":"dWkJQvEoVSj5iz4H"},"_id":"ZTw1HNvVe0dYcEXM","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"dWkJQvEoVSj5iz4H":3}}
{"name":"Power Siphon","type":"feat","img":"icons/magic/symbols/circled-gem-pink.webp","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Starting at 2nd level, you have learned to siphon off some of the energies that would otherwise be wasted when you cast your warmage spells. When you cast a warmage spell of 1st level or higher, you gain a number of siphon motes equal to half the spell's level, rounded up. You can have a number of motes equal to your level in this class at any one time--any extras generated are lost. Your accumulated siphon motes are reset to zero when you finish a long rest.</p><p>Siphon motes can be expended in many ways--each Squad Assignment provides its own uses. The most fundamental use is to empower spells. When you cast a warmage spell of 1st level or higher, you can cast it as if from a higher level slot by expending a number of siphon motes equal to twice the difference between the intended spell slot and the slot you expended. The spell acts as if it was cast out of that higher slot, but you do not regain motes from the cast or expend that higher-level slot. You cannot use this feature to upcast a spell more than one spell level above the highest level of slots you have.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"special","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":2,"max":"@scale.warmage.siphon-mote","per":"lr","recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"class","subtype":""},"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ajpj2HjXWy9aOd8A"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675138643233,"modifiedTime":1675141148233,"lastModifiedBy":"dWkJQvEoVSj5iz4H"},"_id":"ajpj2HjXWy9aOd8A","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"dWkJQvEoVSj5iz4H":3}}
{"name":"Siphon Mastery","type":"feat","img":"icons/magic/symbols/cross-circle-blue.webp","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 20th level, you are even better at using siphoned energy. When you would gain motes normally, you gain twice as many as long as you have less than half your maximum.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"","subtype":""},"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.bEHjxsuzvVkgcocI"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675139457349,"modifiedTime":1675141148236,"lastModifiedBy":"dWkJQvEoVSj5iz4H"},"_id":"bEHjxsuzvVkgcocI","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"dWkJQvEoVSj5iz4H":3}}
{"name":"Way of Living Flame","type":"subclass","img":"icons/magic/fire/flame-burning-fist-strike.webp","system":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif\">An esoteric variant of the Way of the Four Elements that focuses entirely on the properties of flame. Practitioners meditate on the Fountain of Fiery Renewal at the core of the Plane of Flames, connecting with its eternally leaping flames that promise both destruction and rebirth.<br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" /><br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" /><strong style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\">Lambent Strike</strong>: Starting at 3rd level, you can make your ki resonate with elemental fire. When you make an unarmed attack on your turn, you can ignite the ki around body part you strike with. An unarmed strike made this way deals fire damage instead of bludgeoning damage.<br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" /><br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" />When you hit with this strike, you can deal 1d10 additional fire damage. You can add this extra damage a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, regaining expended uses when you finish a long rest. While you have no uses available, you can spend 1 ki point to activate the extra damage again.<br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" /><br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" /><strong style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\">Shedding Sparks</strong> Starting at 3rd level, instead of making an unarmed strike as part of the Attack action or your Martial Arts/Flurry of Blows attacks, you can instead make ranged weapon attacks with flaming ki with a range of 30/120. These ranged attacks deal fire damage as if you had hit with an unarmed strike. You can expend uses of Lambent Strike to deal the same extra damage.<br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" /><br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" /><strong style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\">Ignition Control</strong>: Starting at 3rd level, you can cast the control flames cantrip without needing components. Additionally, you can generate light from your body as if it was a torch, turning it on or off as an action.<br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" /><br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" /><strong style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\">From the Ashes</strong>: Starting at 6th level, you draw on an aspect of eternal renewal. When you use your Step of the Wind, you can choose to heal yourself an amount of hit points equal to two rolls of your martial arts die plus your Wisdom modifier. You can heal in this fashion a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest.<br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" /><br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" />You also gain resistance to fire damage.<br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" /><br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" /><strong style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\">Lightning Dance</strong>: Starting at 11th level, your connection with flame has added an aspect of lighting. This has several effects:<br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" />• When you use Lambent Strike or Shedding Sparks, you can choose to deal lightning damage instead of fire damage.<br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" />• You are resistant to lightning damage in addition to fire damage.<br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" />• You can use your Stunning Strike on the ranged attacks from your Shedding Sparks feature as if they were unarmed strikes.<br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" />• You can spend 3 ki to cast lightning bolt as a 3rd level spell, using your Wisdom as a spellcasting modifier. This does not require any components and can deal either lightning or fire damage as you choose.<br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" /><br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" /><strong style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\">Avatar of Living Flame</strong>: At 17th level, your tie to the Fountain reaches its peak. As a bonus action you can transform into a burning elemental avatar for one minute. You gain the following benefits:<br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" />- <em style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\">Continual Flame</em>: You deal the extra fire or lightning damage on your unarmed and ranged attacks without expending uses of Lambent Strike. Additionally, anyone who touches you or hits you with an attack from within 5 feet takes fire or lightning (your choice) damage equal to 3 rolls of your martial arts die.<br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" />- <em style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\">Rebirth</em>: If you are reduced to 0 hit points or would be killed outright while in this form, the transformation fades and you are restored to full hit points and full ki instead.<br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" />- <em style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\">One with Fire and Lightning</em>: You are immune to fire and lightning.<br style=\"color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial\" />Once you use this feature, you cannot use it again until you finish a long rest.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Dawn of Hope","identifier":"way-of-living-flame","classIdentifier":"monk","advancement":[{"_id":"QT3xH6vVHQ6Y9YqY","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Item.YMIiby2UURDzfRIt","Item.4iZZGlj4ZgKtvEJD","Item.r6B96WxzQJWfkAn5"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":3,"title":"Lambent Body","icon":"icons/magic/fire/flame-burning-hand-orange.webp"},{"_id":"5kcH51t4YTJHQZts","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Item.VZTvTp0K5VjwLONO"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":6,"title":"From the Ashes","icon":"icons/svg/regen.svg"},{"_id":"1pAgvV2B1349RDH4","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Item.P3VqFrhAtKZmVxZM"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":11,"title":""},{"_id":"PvDQqXkhn6eypKfu","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Item.6qHNhQPKsobauQzm"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":17,"title":""}],"spellcasting":{"progression":"none","ability":"wis"}},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675045259473,"modifiedTime":1675050196269,"lastModifiedBy":"dWkJQvEoVSj5iz4H"},"_id":"d7EyNqel2u3G3Dcy","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"dWkJQvEoVSj5iz4H":3}}
{"name":"Enhanced Concentration","type":"feat","img":"icons/magic/control/control-influence-crown-gold.webp","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You gain proficiency in Constitution saving throws.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"","subtype":""},"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[{"label":"CON proficiency","icon":"icons/magic/control/control-influence-crown-gold.webp","origin":"Item.fVCSdAFpAGMIDmpC","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"_id":"idQlPm55kPIIGOrJ","changes":[{"key":"@abilities.con.proficient","mode":5,"value":"true","priority":null}],"tint":null,"transfer":true,"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.fVCSdAFpAGMIDmpC"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675140419817,"modifiedTime":1675141148239,"lastModifiedBy":"dWkJQvEoVSj5iz4H"},"_id":"fVCSdAFpAGMIDmpC","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"dWkJQvEoVSj5iz4H":3}}
{"name":"Line Infantry","type":"subclass","img":"icons/equipment/shield/heater-steel-crystal-red.webp","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Line Infantry squads are in the thickest of the battle and often ordered to hold objectives against overwhelming force. Warmages assigned to Line squads have one primary mission--keep their squad alive against whatever the enemy throws at them. </p><h4>Bonus Spells</h4><p>You gain the following spells known at the indicated levels. These do not count against your spells known limit but cannot be traded out.</p><h4>Line Infantry Spells</h4><p> Level  Spell </p><p>1st   Healing Word </p><p>3rd   Magic Weapon </p><p>5th  Aura of Vitality </p><p>7th  Stoneskin </p><p>9th Mass Cure Wounds</p><h4>Armored Caster</h4><p>When you pick this assignment at first level, you gain proficiency in medium armor and shields and can cast warmage spells while wearing and wielding them. You can use your shield as a focus for your spells.</p><h4>Martial Specialist</h4><p>You gain proficiency in martial weapons.</p><h4>Warding Motes</h4><p>Starting at 6th level, you can expend your siphon motes to shield your allies. As a bonus action on your turn, you can expend one or more motes to create a protective barrier around you until the end of your next turn. This barrier has a radius of 10 ft and hit points equal to the number of motes expended times your proficiency bonus. The barrier has two effects. First, when an effect targets a point in space inside the barrier, it targets the surface of the barrier instead. Second, when a creature within the barrier would take damage from a source outside the barrier, the barrier absorbs that damage as long as it has hit points remaining. If multiple creatures would take damage from the same effect, you can split the absorption effect among those creatures as you choose.</p><p>In addition, when you cast any of your Line Infantry spells while the barrier is active, you can designate an additional ally within the warded zone to receive the benefits of that spell without further cost (including expending additional costly components). If the spell requires concentration and your concentration is broken, both instances of the spell are lost.</p><h4>Enhanced Concentration</h4><p>Starting at 10th level, you gain proficiency in Constitution saving throws.</p><h4>Enhanced Spell Disruption</h4><p>Starting at 14th level, when you cast <em>counterspell</em> or <em>dispel magic</em> and must make a check to see if it succeeds, you do so at advantage.</p><h4>Enhanced Piercing Spell</h4><p>Starting at 18th level, when you use your Piercing Spell feature, the target loses any resistance to the damage type dealt until the beginning of your next turn; if it was immune, it loses that immunity and gains resistance to that damage type until the beginning of your next turn.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","identifier":"line-infantry","classIdentifier":"warmage","advancement":[{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.dnd5e.spells.o8Dh7fblk1d16tnO","Item.yo6jSc3KU1FcgsFy","Item.XR1pud2ykOfgHIBC"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"int","preparation":"always","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":1,"title":"Grant Items","icon":"systems/dnd5e/icons/svg/item-grant.svg","_id":"0kgogHBeoAHzDCsa"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.dnd5e.spells.Sgjrf8qqv97CCWM4"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"int","preparation":"always","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":3,"title":"Bonus Spell 3","icon":"systems/dnd5e/icons/svg/item-grant.svg","_id":"ewcjGD7QW3mWzQhu"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Item.aVg9xUzFM9nDRZOF"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"int","preparation":"always","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":5,"title":"Bonus Spell 5","icon":"systems/dnd5e/icons/svg/item-grant.svg","_id":"UOrZn2gOrSOBDv3P"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.dnd5e.spells.ReMbjfeOKoSj3O79"],"